#### TodoController
**File**: `/back-end/src/app/todo/todo.controller.ts`

**Endpoints**:

| Method | Path | Handler | Description |
|--------|------|---------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/v1/todos` | `index()` | Get all todos |
| POST | `/api/v1/todos` | `create(@Body() body: CreateTodoDto)` | Create new todo |
| GET | `/api/v1/todos/:id` | `show(@Param('id') id: string)` | Get single todo |
| PUT | `/api/v1/todos/:id` | `update(@Param('id') id, @Body() body)` | Update todo |
| DELETE | `/api/v1/todos/:id` | `destroy(@Param('id') id: string)` | Delete todo |

**Controller Patterns**:
```typescript
@Controller('api/v1/todos')
@ApiTags('todos')
export class TodoController {
  constructor(private readonly todoService: TodoService) {}

  // Uses ParseUUIDPipe for ID validation
  async show(@Param('id', new ParseUUIDPipe()) id: string) {...}

  // Comprehensive Swagger documentation with ApiOperation & ApiResponse
  @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Create a new todo' })
  @ApiResponse({ status: 201, type: CreateTodoSwagger })
  @ApiResponse({ status: 400, type: BadRequestSwagger })

  // DELETE returns 204 No Content
  @HttpCode(HttpStatus.NO_CONTENT)
  async destroy(...) {...}
}
```

